<SLUG> BC-BBC-ASU-USC-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
USC BLITZES DEVILS WITH 21-RUN AT TACK 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By PAOLA BOIVIN  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   OMAHA, Neb. _ It was less a battle than an arms race. Whose
pitching could hold out longer?
</P>
<P>
   After an amazing run, Arizona State ran out of steam in the
worst of places: the College World Series, against Southern
California, a team that can rival the Sun Devils for perseverance.
</P>
<P>
   The Trojans won a four-hour tug of war, 21-14, Saturday in front
of a record 24,456 fans at Rosenblatt Stadium and prevented ASU
from capturing its sixth national title and first under Coach Pat
Murphy.
</P>
<P>
   ``Right now, you just don't think there's life after baseball,''
Murphy said.
</P>
<P>
   It was an unlikely ending. In addition to 35 runs, the teams
combined for 39 hits, nine home runs, six wild pitches and, maybe
most telling, 10 pitchers. Thirty-five tournament records fell.
</P>
<P>
   ``Everything about it was crazy,'' ASU pitcher Ryan Mills said.
</P>
<P>
   It was USC's 12th national title _ the most by any school _ and
first since 1978. The Trojans advanced to the championship in 1995
before losing to Cal State-Fullerton.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'll never forget that feeling in '95,'' said USC second
baseman Wes Rachels, who was 5 for 7 against ASU with seven RBIs.
``I was sitting there crying and looking at the faces of the
seniors and thinking, `I never want to feel that.' ''
</P>
<P>
   The Trojans continued postseason domination of ASU. They won
three previous College World Series championship games against ASU:
1-0 in 1972; 4-3 in 1973; and 10-3 in 1978. The win also gave USC a
4-3 edge over ASU this season.
</P>
<P>
   Credit the Sun Devils with moxie. They rallied from a 8-0,
second-inning deficit and trailed just 9-8 after four. They rallied
from a 14-8, sixth-inning deficit to come to within 14-13 in the
seventh.
</P>
<P>
   ``We scored 14 runs and lost,'' Murphy said. ``It's hard to
believe.''
</P>
<P>
   The game never seemed out of reach until the ninth. ASU trailed,
16-14, but reliever Chuck Crumpton gave up a grand slam to Jason
Lane.
</P>
<P>
   Arcadia High School graduate Jack Krawcyzk and his highly
scrutinized ``gravity ball'' kept the Sun Devils hitless for the
final 1 innings to secure his 23rd save, an NCAA record.
</P>
<P>
   ``I threw the pitch I've been throwing all year,'' he said. ``I
was just trying to get the job done. There was no wind and I knew
they most likely would score some runs.''
</P>
<P>
   ASU starter Mills only lasted an inning, allowing six runs and
six hits. He was followed by Aaron Kramer (five innings), Chad
Pennington (1), Phill Lowery (1) and Crumpton (two-thirds).
</P>
<P>
   ``I knew when I was warming up that I didn't have it,'' Mills
said. ``But I was going to go out there and give it everything I
had.''
</P>
<P>
   Other than Krawcyzk, USC's pitchers also struggled, but the
offense more than made up for it.
</P>
<P>
   In addition to the grand slam, a seventh-inning triple steal
also seemed to zap life out of ASU.
</P>
<P>
   ASU didn't have the hits, but it had the karma. Murphy had in
his possession a ring from the 1977 ASU championship team. He
received it from Bob Horner, a second baseman from that club.
</P>
<P>
   ``We still accomplished a lot,'' third baseman Andrew Beinbrink
said. ``A lot of people didn't believe in us, but we always
believed in ourselves. We played some really great baseball in the
regional and in Omaha. Today, we didn't do some of the things that
had made us successful.
</P>
<P>
   ``Our season says a lot for ASU and how to play the game.''
</P>
<P>
   Indeed, the Sun Devils made an improbable run this year. If they
had won the title, they would have had the lowest winning
percentage of any champion.
</P>
<P>
   At midseason, this team was only two games above .500. But it
battled all season and continued to find ways to win.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm just so proud of these guys,'' Murphy said. ``It's no fun
to lose, it's tough, but somehow you have to look for all the good
in everything. People counted this team out so many times, but they
battled back.''
</P>
<P>
   Murphy again must restock a team that is losing many of its
stars, including Mills, Beinbrink and Mikel Moreno.
</P>
<P>
   ``Credit USC,'' Murphy said. ``They were awesome.''
</P>
<P>
   It was an amazing postseason run for the Trojans, who lost their
opener to Louisiana State but came back to beat Florida and
Mississippi State. They had to beat LSU on consecutive days and
did.
</P>
<P>
   ``We couldn't allow ourselves a week ago to think that we would
be playing today in the national championship,'' Gillespie said.
``This achievement for me goes beyond my ability to describe it.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
