<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBC-ASU-MILLS-CWS-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WARM-UPS BAD SIGN FOR ASU ACE MILLS  
 PITCHER SAYS HE FEARED WHAT WAS TO COME 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By PAOLA BOIVIN  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   OMAHA, Neb. _ Ryan Mills knew.
</P>
<P>
   He knew during warm-ups that his arm didn't have it.
</P>
<P>
   ``But I felt crappy against Miami, too, and I still wanted to
pitch,'' the Arizona State left-hander said.
</P>
<P>
   Mills lasted just one inning in Saturday's 21-14 College World
Series loss to Miami. He allowed six runs and six hits and struck
out one.
</P>
<P>
   Mills' postseason has been a roller-coaster ride.
</P>
<P>
   He was dominating in a complete-game three-hitter against
Georgia Tech in the Midwest Regional championship game.
</P>
<P>
   He gave the Sun Devils a solid six innings in their College
World Series contest against the Hurricanes. He wasn't as sharp as
in his previous outing, but was effective enough for the victory.
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought if I could do it in that game, I might as well try
here,'' he said. ``It just didn't happen.''
</P>
<P>
   ASU Coach Pat Murphy said he was hesitant before the game about
allowing Mills to pitch, but history had suggested that letting the
junior go was the right decision.
</P>
<P>
   ``Part of me said today, `It's going to be a lot to ask. SC
knows him so well,' '' Murphy said. ``But I just know what he's
done for us in the past, so . . .''
</P>
<P>
   Mills was pitching on six days of rest. Ultimately, it wasn't
enough.
</P>
<P>
   He finished with an 8-4 record this season and a career mark of
27-21.
</P>
<P>
   It has been a bittersweet week. On Tuesday, he was the sixth
overall pick in the draft by the Minnesota Twins. He is expected to
receive a $2 million signing bonus.
</P>
<P>
   Earlier this week, Mills said winning a College World Series
``would mean a lot more than getting drafted.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It's tough, but you're going to have these times in your
life,'' he said. ``It's hard to think about now, but I know I'm
fortunate to have been a part of this. A lot of people can't say
that.
</P>
<P>
   ``This team has a lot to feel good about. We've accomplished a
lot this year. We fought until the end.''
</P>
<P>
   Mills is used to dealing with adversity.
</P>
<P>
   He was hit in the face by a line drive in the first inning of
his first start as a freshman and made only three appearances the
rest of the season.
</P>
<P>
   He came back as a sophomore to post a 6-3 mark and 2.88 ERA.
</P>
<P>
   He was unable to pitch in the second championship game against
Miami in the Atlantic Regional last season because his arm didn't
have it. It wasn't a decision he wanted to make but felt it was the
best for the team, even though some criticized him for it.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm proud of what he's done for us this season,'' ASU Coach
Pat Murphy said. ``He's dealt with a lot. He's a winner, and that's
why I think he's someone who will have success in the future.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
