<P>
   BOAT-EXCAVATION _ Texas A&AMP;M archeologists have begun the
exploration for excavation of the Civil War-era blockade runner
Denbigh, a 182-foot converted merchant vessel. It was one of the
most successful blockade runners -- penetrating the line of Union
ships blockading the Texas coast -- until it ran aground off
Bolivar Point while trying to enter Galveston Harbor near the end
of the war. (Stanley, Austin American-Statesman). 25.
</P>
