<P>
   BATTERED-VICTIMS (Los Angeles) _ Waiting to testify as a
reluctant witness in a criminal case, Veronica Martinez spent five
hours in a small holding cell and was led to a courtroom in
handcuffs. She was the victim in a domestic violence case. Her case
represents a trend since the O.J. Simpson trial in which
prosecutors and judges are getting aggressive with victims
themselves. By Alex Roth. (Will move in the ``n'' California and
``a'' national news files.)
</P>
